  "body": "**Issue Template**\r\n\r\n*Title*: The behavior documents for Envoy::Network::Address::Instance::bind() is not followed by Instance implementations.\r\n\r\n*Description*:\r\nThe documentation for Envoy::Network::Address::Instance::bind() says:\r\n   * @return the platform error code.\r\nHowever, the implementation of ...::Ipv6Instance::bind() (e.g.) is:\r\n\r\n  return ::bind(fd, reinterpret_cast<const sockaddr*>(&ip_.ipv6_.address_),\r\n                sizeof(ip_.ipv6_.address_));\r\n\r\nAccording to the bind(2) man page, on unix at least this returns either 0 (success) or -1 (error), and if a -1 is returned the error code is in errno.h.  See for instance http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/bind.2.html.  This seems in conflict with the envoy documentation.\r\n\r\n",
